[normal]&#xa0;[bold]About the Sex Education Forum[bold]The Sex Education Forum
[normal], hosted by the National Children’s Bureau, is the national authority on sex and relationships education (SRE). It is a unique collaboration of national organisations and practitioners with representatives from health, education, faith, disability and chil
[normal]dren's organisations.  The Sex Education Forum believes that all children and young people have the right to good SRE and aims to provide all professionals involved in SRE with the information they need to ensure this right.
